Metric Idea When it matters Precision Fraction of retrieved items that are relevant Spammy results hurt precision Recall Fraction of relevant items that are retrieved Missing the right doc hurts recall Precision@K / Recall@K Same, but only top-K Standard for ranked lists AP (Average Precision) Area under precision-recall curve for a query Aggregated → MAP across queries MRR Mean reciprocal rank of the first relevant result Great for navigational queries (“facebook login”) NDCG@K Normalized Discounted Cumulative Gain at K Gold standard when multiple relevance levels and position matter <p>DCG rewards putting highly relevant items high; IDCG is the ideal DCG; NDCG = DCG/IDCG.</p> <pre><code>import math
from typing import Iterable, List


def dcg_at_k(relevance_scores: List[float], k: int) -&gt; float:
    """relevance_scores: best-first list of graded relevance (e.g. 0,1,2,3)."""
    return sum(
        (2 ** rel - 1) / math.log2(idx + 2)
        for idx, rel in enumerate(relevance_scores[:k])
    )


def ndcg_at_k(relevance_scores: List[float], ideal_scores: List[float], k: int) -&gt; float:
    ideal_scores = sorted(ideal_scores, reverse=True)
    idcg = dcg_at_k(ideal_scores, k)
    if idcg == 0:
        return 0.0
    return dcg_at_k(relevance_scores, k) / idcg
